The American Paranormal

Investigative Journalism from the Shadows of America's Hidden History

Journey into the unexplained corners of America where reality bends and the impossible becomes tangible. Through meticulous investigation and eyewitness accounts, this groundbreaking work examines the paranormal phenomena that has shaped our nation's hidden history—from haunted battlefields to cryptid encounters in the wilderness. Featuring collaboration with renowned evidential medium Cindy Kaza.

Inside the Investigation

📋

Documented Cases

Over 200 meticulously researched paranormal incidents across 45 states, including the Greenbrier Ghost (1897) - the only U.S. murder trial where ghost testimony led to conviction, and the Bell Witch haunting (1817-1828) - the most documented paranormal case in American history. Each case backed by witness testimony, court records, and on-site investigation.

🔍

Field Research

Decades of boots-on-the-ground investigation in America's most haunted locations including Gettysburg Battlefield, the Stanley Hotel, Eastern State Penitentiary, and Mount Vernon. Using EVP recordings, EMF detection, thermal imaging, and full-spectrum photography to document firsthand encounters with the unexplained.

⚖️

Expert Analysis

Collaboration with leading researchers, historians, and mediums including evidential medium Cindy Kaza, trained at England's prestigious Arthur Findlay School. A scientific approach combining parapsychology, forensic analysis, and historical documentation to separate fact from fiction in paranormal phenomena.

Featured Collaboration

Cindy Kaza

Evidential Medium • TV Personality

Cindy Kaza is a renowned evidential medium and clairvoyant who brings her extraordinary abilities to The American Paranormal. Trained at England's prestigious Arthur Findlay School of Intuitive Sciences, Cindy is known for her work on Travel Channel's The Dead Files and The Holzer Files, where she combines mediumship with paranormal investigation.

As a clairvoyant, clairaudient, and clairsentient, Cindy provides highly specific evidence during readings to diminish skepticism and prove authentic connections with spirits. Her chapter in The American Paranormal explores the intersection of evidential mediumship and paranormal investigation, offering readers documented encounters that bridge the gap between the living and the spirit world.

Featured TV Appearances: The Dead Files, The Holzer Files, Paranormal Mysteries, Portals to Hell, Ghost Brothers, The Osbournes: Night of Terror

About the Author

Ph.D. in History • Former Law Enforcement

Dr. Stephen Dietrich-Kolokouris is a historian, author, and investigator whose works explore the darkest intersections of history, crime, and the unexplained. With a Ph.D. in history and extensive background in law enforcement, he brings both scholarly rigor and investigative expertise to his research.

His groundbreaking books span from paranormal investigations and true crime to suppressed histories of World War II. Featured in Esquire Magazine Australia, Dr. Dietrich-Kolokouris's writing offers both gripping storytelling and deep investigative insight.

  • Ph.D. in History
  • Former Law Enforcement Officer
  • Featured in Esquire Magazine Australia
  • Specialist in Paranormal Investigation & True Crime

When not writing, Dr. Dietrich-Kolokouris can be found in historical archives or exploring the stories that continue to shape our understanding of the unexplained and the hidden truths of our past.
